tspan.tspan: This is your aircraft ID. Please register it at http://ddb.glidernet.org in order to see your aircraft
registration in tracking websites.
This device allows you to publish your aircraft position on Open Glider Network and make it visible
on various tracking websites, such as http://glidertracker.org or http://flightradar24.com. Visit
http://glidernet.org for more information about how Open Glider Network works.
Your device is equipped with Bluetooth module. It lets you easily connect the device to your
smartphone running a navigation software, such as XCSoar. To connect via bluetooth, use this
information:
Name: Ked Tracker $aid
RJ-45 socket can be used to power the device from
the onboard battery, connect external FLARM
viewer or electronic variometer. Pinout adheres to
IGC standart.
By Andrey Lebedev in 2018.
Project maintained at https://github.com/kedder/kedtracker/ and distributed under Terms and Conditions of GPL v3 license. Based on design of
OGN project, see http://wiki.glidernet.org/ogn-tracker-diy.
Made in Lithuania.
For best range install the device so that antenna is oriented vertically. Make sure antenna is fully
screwed in and not touching any external objects. Install the device in the location that is not
surrounded by materials that may obstruct radio waves, such as metal or carbon fiber.
